pi.github.com/users/mloning/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mloning/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mloning/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mloning/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mloning/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mloning/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mloning/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mloning/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mloning/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2021-02-24T13:42:33Z","updated_at":"2021-02-24T13:42:33Z","author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"Thanks for your issue @rjafarau - feedback and improvement suggestions are very welcome!\r\n\r\nIn case you haven't seen it, we've summarised some of the motivations behind our design choices [here](https://github.com/sktime/enhancement-proposals/blob/master/steps/01_forecasting_api/model-evaluation-tuning.md). \r\n\r\n1. This is work in progress, we need to implement the same mechanism we have for the `evaluate` function inside of `ForecastingGridSearchCV`.\r\n2. See my answer to 5\r\n3. That is also work in progress, supporting multi-step forecasting horizons adds some complication in terms of aggregating performance metrics.\r\n4. `evaluate` is meant to be used instead of `cross_val_score` - we can reconsider naming, but we wanted to make a clear distinction between model selection and model evaluation, something which isn't clearly distinguished in scikit-learn for example.\r\n5. As far as I can see, there are the following main strategies: \r\n* blocked cross-validation, random subsampling with some distance between training and test windows,\r\n* sliding windows, re-fitting the model for each training window,\r\n* sliding windows with an initial window, using the initial window for training and subsequent windows for updating,\r\n* expanding windows, refitting the model for each training window.\r\n\r\nThat's why we have the initial window parameter. Your help is very welcome if you think about contributing! ","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/comments/785083718/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"mloning","id":21020482,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIxMDIwNDgy","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/21020482?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mloning","html_url":"https://github.com/mloning","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mloning/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mloning/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mloning/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mloning/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mloning/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mloning/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mloning/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mloning/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mloning/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false}},{"id":4371013592,"node_id":"MDE0Ok1lbnRpb25lZEV2ZW50NDM3MTAxMzU5Mg==","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/events/4371013592","actor":{"login":"rjafarau","id":16004173,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE2MDA0MTcz","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/16004173?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/rjafarau","html_url":"https://github.com/rjafarau","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rjafarau/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rjafarau/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rjafarau/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rjafarau